00:10.552 --> 00:13.722
ONLY FOUR DAYS UNTIL CHRISTMAS, AND IT'S A COLD ONE OUT THERE!

00:13.763 --> 00:15.056
BUT TO WARM US UP,

00:15.056 --> 00:16.641
HERE ARE THE SOOTHING SOUNDS OF MR. MICHAEL BUBLE!

00:16.683 --> 00:18.643
♪ SLEIGH BELLS RING

00:18.685 --> 00:20.562
♪ ARE YOU LISTENIN'?

00:20.562 --> 00:22.230
♪ IN THE LANE

00:22.272 --> 00:24.733
♪ SNOW IS GLISTENIN'

00:24.774 --> 00:26.443
♪ A BEAUTIFUL SIGHT

00:26.484 --> 00:28.570
♪ WE'RE HAPPY TONIGHT

00:28.611 --> 00:31.990
♪ WALKIN'IN A WINTER WONDERLAND ♪

00:32.031 --> 00:35.577
♪ GONE AWAYIS THE BLUE BIRD ♪

00:35.618 --> 00:39.789
♪ HERE TO STAYIS A NEW BIRD ♪

00:39.831 --> 00:41.750
♪ TO SING A LOVE SONG

00:41.750 --> 00:43.752
♪ WHILE WE STROLL ALONG

00:43.793 --> 00:47.630
♪ WALKIN'IN A WINTER WONDERLAND ♪

00:47.672 --> 00:50.592
♪ IN THE MEADOWWE CAN BUILD A SNOWMAN... ♪

00:50.633 --> 00:52.343
-TOM.-HEY, HELEN.

00:52.385 --> 00:53.344
CAN YOU TAKE US WITH YOU?

00:53.386 --> 00:55.972
WITH A FAMILY LIKE YOURS,

00:56.014 --> 00:57.515
I WOULD NEVERWANT TO GO ANYWHERE.

00:57.557 --> 00:58.475
THESE GO UNDER THE TREE.

00:58.516 --> 01:00.643
OH, YOUSHOULDN'T HAVE.

01:00.685 --> 01:01.811
AND HERE'S THIS GUY.

01:01.853 --> 01:03.021
MM-HMM.

01:03.063 --> 01:04.522
WELL, WE'LL TAKEGOOD CARE OF HER FOR YOU.

01:04.563 --> 01:05.522
YOU ALWAYS DO.

01:05.565 --> 01:06.941
THANKS, HELEN.

01:06.983 --> 01:08.443
I LOVED THAT ARTICLEON SOFAS YOU DID

01:08.443 --> 01:09.444
IN THELADIES' WEEKLY.

01:09.486 --> 01:12.530
OH, YOU'RE TOO KIND.

01:12.572 --> 01:13.615
MERRY CHRISTMAS, HELEN.

01:13.656 --> 01:14.616
THANK YOU.

01:14.616 --> 01:16.826
YOU TOO, TOM.

01:25.001 --> 01:26.628
DO YOU REALLY NEEDALL THAT STUFF?

01:26.628 --> 01:27.837
YOU KNOWI'M AN OVER-PACKER.

01:27.879 --> 01:29.506
I KNOW YOU'REAN OVER-SPENDER.

01:29.547 --> 01:31.466
UH, MR. POWERS?

01:31.466 --> 01:33.343
YOU'RE MAX POWERS,THE MOVIE DIRECTOR, RIGHT?

01:33.384 --> 01:35.136
GUILTY AS CHARGED.

01:35.136 --> 01:37.555
WOW. I'VE SEENEVERY ONE OF YOUR FILMS.

01:37.597 --> 01:39.390
CAN I GETA SELFIE?

01:39.432 --> 01:41.810
SURE.

01:41.810 --> 01:43.520
ARE YOU ANYONE?

01:43.561 --> 01:45.480
NO.

01:45.522 --> 01:47.148
[CLICK]

01:47.190 --> 01:48.399
THANKS!

01:51.402 --> 01:52.904
I STILL CANNOT BELIEVE

01:52.946 --> 01:55.156
YOU TALKED ME INTO FLYINGALL THE WAY FROM L.A.

01:55.156 --> 01:56.825
JUST TO RIDE THE TRAINBACK HOME WITH YOU.

01:56.825 --> 01:59.160
HOW ELSE ARE YOU GOING TO WRITEA SCRIPT ABOUT A TRAIN?

01:59.202 --> 02:01.079
LOOK, I REALLY APPRECIATETHE OPPORTUNITY,

02:01.120 --> 02:03.373
BUT I THINK YOU SHOULDPROBABLY FIND SOMEBODY ELSE.

02:03.414 --> 02:05.375
I MEAN,I'M A SCRIPT DOCTOR.

02:05.416 --> 02:08.002
I HELP FIXOTHER PEOPLE'S MOVIES.

02:08.002 --> 02:09.169
I DON'T THINK I'M READYTO WRITE ONE MYSELF.

02:09.211 --> 02:10.255
ELEANOR...

02:10.295 --> 02:12.006
YOU KNOW YOU'RE THE DAUGHTERTHAT I NEVER HAD.

02:12.006 --> 02:13.341
YOU HAVE FOUR KIDS.

02:13.341 --> 02:14.342
ALL BOYS,

02:14.342 --> 02:15.593
AND SINCE YOU'RE LIKEA DAUGHTER TO ME,

02:15.635 --> 02:16.719
I CAN TELL YOU,

02:16.761 --> 02:18.012
YOU HAVE CONFIDENCE ISSUES.

02:18.012 --> 02:19.013
MAX...

02:19.013 --> 02:20.056
YOU'RE TOO GOOD

02:20.098 --> 02:21.599
TO BE RE-WRITINGOTHER PEOPLE'S STORIES.

02:21.641 --> 02:23.601
IT'S TIME YOU PUTYOUR NAME ON SOMETHING,

02:23.643 --> 02:25.228
AND WHAT A BETTER WAYTO START

02:25.270 --> 02:29.315
THAN ROMANCEON A TRAIN?

02:32.151 --> 02:33.611
OKAY...

02:38.700 --> 02:41.536
I FEEL SOMETHING MAGICALHAPPENING FOR YOU

02:41.578 --> 02:43.371
THIS CHRISTMAS EVE.

02:43.371 --> 02:44.372
THAT'S OUR WEDDING DAY!

02:44.414 --> 02:45.373
IS IT?

02:45.415 --> 02:46.875
-HOW DID YOU KNOW?-OH, MY GOODNESS!

02:46.875 --> 02:49.043
[LAUGHING]

02:49.085 --> 02:52.630
[♪♪]

03:08.229 --> 03:10.815
LOOKS LIKE WE'LL BELEAVING RIGHT ON TIME.

03:10.857 --> 03:11.733
THAT'S GOOD.

03:11.774 --> 03:12.942
YES, CERTAINLY IS.

03:12.984 --> 03:14.110
PEOPLE RELY ON US,YOU KNOW.

03:14.152 --> 03:15.528
YOU WORKFOR THE TRAINS?

03:15.570 --> 03:17.447
DID,

03:17.488 --> 03:18.740
FOR MOST OF MY LIFE.

03:18.740 --> 03:20.742
I'M JUST A PASSENGER NOW.

03:20.783 --> 03:21.993
YOU RIDE OFTEN?

03:22.035 --> 03:24.913
WELL, IT'S BEEN A WHILE...

03:24.913 --> 03:25.914
10 YEARS.

03:25.914 --> 03:27.332
OH, THATIS A WHILE.

03:27.373 --> 03:28.458
YEAH.

03:28.499 --> 03:30.960
ACTUALLY, I THOUGHTI'D NEVER GET ON ONE AGAIN.

03:31.002 --> 03:32.670
AH. TOO MANY STOPS?

03:32.712 --> 03:35.715
TOO MANY STOPS, YOU MIGHT SAY.

03:36.758 --> 03:37.675
TOM LANGDON.

03:37.717 --> 03:38.760
HERRICK HIGGINS.

03:38.760 --> 03:39.928
MY FRIENDSCALL ME HIGGINS.

03:39.928 --> 03:40.929
HIGGINS IT IS.

03:40.929 --> 03:41.888
[PHONE RINGS]

03:45.183 --> 03:46.100
-EXCUSE ME.-YEAH.

03:46.142 --> 03:47.185
HIGGINS.

03:50.104 --> 03:51.272
HI, LELIA.

03:51.272 --> 03:52.357
I WAS JUST ABOUT TO CALL YOU.

03:52.398 --> 03:54.317
PLEASE TELL MEYOU'RE NOT CANCELING.

03:54.359 --> 03:55.443
NO, NO, I'LL BE THERE.

03:55.443 --> 03:57.695
CHRISTMAS DAY,JUST LIKE WE PLANNED.

03:57.737 --> 03:59.781
IN FACT, I'M LEAVING NOW...ON A TRAIN.

03:59.781 --> 04:00.740
WHAT?

04:00.782 --> 04:02.325
I'M TAKING THE TRAIN.

04:02.367 --> 04:03.952
ALL THE WAY TO LOS ANGELES?

04:03.993 --> 04:04.953
YOU CAN'T BE SERIOUS.

04:04.953 --> 04:06.287
IT'S FOR A STORY.

04:06.287 --> 04:07.622
SO YOU NEED TO BE ON A TRAIN

04:07.664 --> 04:09.374
TO WRITE A STORY?

04:09.415 --> 04:12.961
YES, IT'S A STORYABOUT CHRISTMAS ON A TRAIN.

04:12.961 --> 04:13.962
[SIGHS]

04:13.962 --> 04:14.879
I'LL BE THERE. I PROMISE.

04:14.921 --> 04:16.589
I HOPE SO.

04:20.635 --> 04:22.470
RELATIONSHIP PROBLEMS?

04:24.347 --> 04:25.348
EXCUSE ME?

04:25.390 --> 04:26.641
I'M SORRY, I JUST--

04:26.683 --> 04:27.850
I COULDN'T HELPBUT OVERHEAR.

04:27.892 --> 04:28.768
WAS THAT YOUR WIFE?

04:30.478 --> 04:31.771
NO.

04:34.274 --> 04:36.234
GIRLFRIEND, THEN.

04:38.236 --> 04:40.530
HOW MUCH DID YOUACTUALLY OVERHEAR?

04:40.571 --> 04:42.824
OH, YOU KNOW, JUST...LIKE, A TAD.

04:42.865 --> 04:43.908
A TAD?

04:43.950 --> 04:44.826
EVERYTHING.

04:44.826 --> 04:46.327
EVERYTHING.

04:46.327 --> 04:47.245
BUT DON'T WORRY.

04:47.286 --> 04:48.079
IT'LL ALL COME OUTON THE TRAIN.

04:48.121 --> 04:49.205
IT ALWAYS DOES.

04:49.247 --> 04:51.749
ALL ABOARD!

04:57.839 --> 04:59.507
THERE'S A GUY DOWN THEREWRITING A STORY.

05:01.134 --> 05:02.844
-ABOUT THE CHRISTMAS TRAIN!-OH!

05:02.885 --> 05:04.804
YES. OH, YES, SORRY.

05:10.226 --> 05:11.185
WELCOME ABOARD.

05:11.185 --> 05:12.770
WHAT'S THAT,A CHRISTMAS CAROL?

05:12.812 --> 05:14.188
YES.

05:14.188 --> 05:16.190
I HAVEN'T READ THAT ONEIN A LONG TIME.

05:16.190 --> 05:17.275
IT'S MY WIFE'S.

05:17.317 --> 05:19.527
I PROMISED HER THATI'D RE-READ THE CLASSICS.

05:19.527 --> 05:20.737
A LOFTY GOAL.

05:20.778 --> 05:22.864
AFRAID I HAVEN'TSTARTED YET.

05:22.905 --> 05:24.574
WELCOME ABOARD, MR. KELLY.

05:26.409 --> 05:28.369
WELCOME ABOARD,MR... LANGDON.

05:28.411 --> 05:30.079
THANK YOU, AND IT'S TOM.

05:30.121 --> 05:31.706
TOM. I HEARYOU'RE WRITING A STORY

05:31.706 --> 05:32.832
ABOUT THECHRISTMAS TRAIN.

05:32.874 --> 05:34.375
WORD TRAVELS FASTAROUND HERE.

05:34.375 --> 05:35.918
YOU HAVE NO IDEA.

05:35.960 --> 05:37.295
YOU'RE INCOMPARTMENT D.

05:37.336 --> 05:38.296
GREAT.

05:38.338 --> 05:39.380
YOU'RE RIGHT NEXT TO ME.

05:39.422 --> 05:40.381
GOOD.

05:40.423 --> 05:41.382
GREAT.

05:41.424 --> 05:43.468
DON'T WORRY,YOU'LL GET TO KNOW AGNES,

05:43.509 --> 05:44.469
WHETHER YOU WANT TOOR NOT.

05:44.510 --> 05:45.511
MERRY CHRISTMAS.

06:15.291 --> 06:16.250
HEY.

06:16.292 --> 06:18.586
DON'T TELL MEYOU ALREADY STARTED WRITING.

06:18.586 --> 06:21.964
WELL, IF YOU CONSIDERSTARING AT A BLANK PAGE WRITING,

06:22.006 --> 06:22.965
THEN YES.

06:23.007 --> 06:24.050
I HOPEYOU'RE NOT PLANNING

06:24.092 --> 06:26.094
TO DO THIS WHOLE THINGFROM YOUR ROOM.

06:26.094 --> 06:29.263
THE INSPIRATION IS OUT THERE,NOT IN HERE.

06:29.263 --> 06:31.099
MAX, WE HAVEN'T EVENLEFT THE STATION YET.

06:31.099 --> 06:31.933
EXACTLY,

06:31.974 --> 06:33.559
SO LIVE A LITTLE.

06:33.601 --> 06:34.769
TAKE IT IN.

06:34.811 --> 06:37.021
IS THIS HOW IT'S GOING TO BETHE WHOLE WAY?

06:37.063 --> 06:38.439
I'VE BEEN MAKING MOVIESFOR A LONG TIME,

06:38.481 --> 06:41.651
AND YOU KNOW THE ONE WORDTHAT STARTS EVERYTHING OFF?

06:41.692 --> 06:43.194
"ACTION"?

06:43.236 --> 06:45.279
NO.

06:45.321 --> 06:46.447
"HELLO."

06:46.447 --> 06:48.491
I'LL BE INTHE LOUNGE CAR,

06:48.533 --> 06:51.160
CAVORTINGWITH MY FELLOW PASSENGERS.

06:51.202 --> 06:52.620
[LAUGHS] OKAY.

06:53.496 --> 06:54.330
HAVE FUN.

06:54.372 --> 06:55.540
[CHUCKLES]

06:59.919 --> 07:02.964
"AND SO IT BEGINS,

07:03.005 --> 07:04.799
"A 3,000-MILE TREKACROSS AMERICA

07:04.799 --> 07:07.343
"IN FOUR DAYS.

07:07.385 --> 07:10.805
I HOPE THERE'S A STORY HERE."

07:24.110 --> 07:25.987
DO I HAVE TO PAY A TOLLTO PASS THROUGH?

07:26.028 --> 07:27.029
SORRY.

07:27.071 --> 07:28.489
OH, DON'T BE.

07:28.489 --> 07:29.490
IT'S NICE TO SEE

07:29.490 --> 07:30.700
TWO YOUNG PEOPLE

07:30.741 --> 07:31.701
WHO CAN'T LIVEWITHOUT EACH OTHER.

07:31.742 --> 07:33.286
AND WE WON'T, WILL WE?

07:34.328 --> 07:35.913
WE'RE GETTING MARRIEDON THE TRAIN.

07:35.955 --> 07:36.998
CONGRATULATIONS!

07:37.039 --> 07:38.624
IS THE WHOLE WEDDING PARTYON BOARD?

07:38.666 --> 07:39.667
NO,

07:39.667 --> 07:40.668
JUST US.

07:40.668 --> 07:42.545
WELL, THAT'S ALL YOU NEED,RIGHT?

07:42.587 --> 07:44.380
I'M STEVE, AND THAT'S JULIE.

07:44.422 --> 07:45.381
TOM,

07:45.423 --> 07:47.175
AND THIS IS AGNES.

07:47.216 --> 07:48.384
CONGRATULATIONS!

07:48.426 --> 07:49.427
YEAH, EXCUSE ME.

07:49.468 --> 07:50.595
PARDON ME.

07:50.636 --> 07:51.971
-HELLO.-HELLO.

07:52.013 --> 07:53.055
HI.

07:53.097 --> 07:56.184
YEP... AGNES.

08:02.190 --> 08:05.735
AND REMEMBER,TUESDAY IS YOUR LUCKY DAY.

08:05.776 --> 08:07.111
WHAT'S MY LUCKY DAY?

08:07.153 --> 08:08.196
HAVE A SEAT AND I'LL TELL YOU.

08:08.196 --> 08:09.238
YOU'RE A PSYCHIC?

08:09.280 --> 08:11.073
I KNOW THINGS.

08:11.115 --> 08:12.033
YOU COULD CALL IT INTUITION.

08:12.074 --> 08:14.452
I'M KIND OFMORE OF A FACT GUY.

08:14.494 --> 08:15.953
HMM.

08:15.995 --> 08:19.123
THAT MIGHT CHANGEALONG THE WAY.

08:23.377 --> 08:24.879
[BARTENDER]:WHAT ARE YOU DRINKING?

08:24.879 --> 08:26.172
WHAT DO YOU GOT?

08:26.214 --> 08:27.298
UH, WE GOT SANTA-TINI,

08:27.340 --> 08:29.509
THE RED RUDOLPH,THE GRINCH...

08:29.550 --> 08:30.384
WHAT'S IN THE GRINCH?

08:30.384 --> 08:31.385
DRINK ONE

08:31.385 --> 08:32.428
AND YOU'LL THINK EVERY DAYIS CHRISTMAS.

08:32.470 --> 08:33.971
I'LL HAVE A GRINCH.

08:34.013 --> 08:36.557
MAKE THAT TWO.

08:36.557 --> 08:38.893
HEY, IS THAT THE ORIGINAL

08:38.893 --> 08:40.602
P42 CAP ENGINE?

08:40.645 --> 08:43.648
16 CYLINDERS,4,250 HORSEPOWER?

08:43.688 --> 08:44.649
RIGHT YOU ARE.

08:44.690 --> 08:45.650
WHAT THAT THINGCOULDN'T OUTRUN,

08:45.691 --> 08:47.693
IT WOULD RUN RIGHT OVER.

08:47.735 --> 08:49.237
YOU'RE A TRAIN MAN, HUH?

08:49.237 --> 08:52.406
AH, WELL, MY DADHAD A THING FOR THE TRAINS.

08:52.448 --> 08:53.658
MINE TOO.

08:53.699 --> 08:55.284
HE PUT ME ON ONEWHEN I WAS 16

08:55.326 --> 08:56.619
AND TOLD ME, "DON'T COME BACK

08:56.661 --> 08:58.204
UNTIL YOU MAKE SOMETHINGOF YOURSELF."

08:59.622 --> 09:00.790
MAX POWERS.

09:00.831 --> 09:01.916
THE DIRECTOR?

09:01.958 --> 09:03.125
GUILTY AS CHARGED.

09:03.167 --> 09:04.377
I'M A BIG FAN.

09:04.418 --> 09:05.253
TOM LANGDON.

09:05.294 --> 09:06.254
TOM, WHEREARE YOU HEADING?

09:06.254 --> 09:07.255
L.A.

09:07.296 --> 09:08.339
I'M GUESSING

09:08.381 --> 09:09.590
YOU'RE NOT IN ANY BIG HURRYTO GET THERE?

09:09.590 --> 09:11.092
WHY DO YOU SAY THAT?

09:11.092 --> 09:12.593
YOU ARE TAKING A TRAIN.

09:12.635 --> 09:14.387
RIGHT.

09:14.428 --> 09:17.640
WELL, I'M ACTUALLY ON BOARDLOOKING FOR A STORY.

09:17.682 --> 09:19.267
YOU'RE A WRITER?

09:19.308 --> 09:21.102
UM, A JOURNALIST,

09:21.143 --> 09:22.311
OR AT LEAST I WAS.

09:22.353 --> 09:25.773
I WAS A WAR CORRESPONDENT,WAY BACK WHEN.

09:25.815 --> 09:28.526
NOW THE MOSTDANGEROUS THING I COVER

09:28.567 --> 09:30.611
IS THE HAZARDOUS PITFALLSOF HOME BARBECUING.

09:32.822 --> 09:34.198
WHO'S THIS ONE FOR?

09:35.575 --> 09:36.826
THIS ONE'S FOR MY DAD...

09:36.867 --> 09:37.827
HIS LAST WISH.

09:37.868 --> 09:38.953
MM.

09:38.995 --> 09:40.454
MARK TWAINIS A DISTANT RELATIVE,

09:40.454 --> 09:41.581
AND APPARENTLY,

09:41.622 --> 09:43.624
HE WANTED TO WRITE A STORYABOUT TRAIN TRAVEL

09:43.624 --> 09:44.625
AND NEVER DID,

09:44.667 --> 09:46.127
SO HOPEFULLY I CAN.

09:46.127 --> 09:47.670
THERE'S SOMETHINGABOUT A TRAIN, RIGHT?

09:47.712 --> 09:49.130
THERE IS.

09:49.130 --> 09:51.132
MY NEXT MOVIE'SGOING TO TAKE PLACE ON ONE.

09:51.173 --> 09:52.174
OH, WOW.

09:52.216 --> 09:55.011
YOU KNOW,I JUST HAD A BRAINSTORM.

09:56.345 --> 09:57.972
YOU AND MY WRITERSHOULD TEAM UP,

09:57.972 --> 09:59.807
I MEAN, JUSTFOR THE RESEARCH PART--

09:59.807 --> 10:02.893
SWAP NOTES,STORIES YOU'VE HEARD,

10:02.935 --> 10:07.982
AND THE PULSE OF AMERICAON A TRAIN.

10:07.982 --> 10:09.859
WELL, THANK YOUFOR THE OFFER,

10:09.900 --> 10:11.110
BUT, UH...

10:11.152 --> 10:13.029
I'M MORE ACCUSTOMEDTO WORKING ALONE.

10:13.070 --> 10:14.030
OF COURSE,I'LL PAY YOU.

10:14.071 --> 10:15.489
NO, NO, IT'S NOT THAT.

10:15.531 --> 10:18.367
I DID HAVE A PARTNER ONCE,

10:18.409 --> 10:20.870
AND, WELL, IT JUSTDIDN'T WORK OUT THAT WELL.

10:20.911 --> 10:22.830
YEAH, I UNDERSTAND.

10:22.872 --> 10:24.707
I HAD A FEW PARTNERS MYSELF,

10:24.749 --> 10:29.295
BUT AT LEASTJOIN US FOR DINNER TONIGHT.

10:30.338 --> 10:32.423
HOW COULD I SAY NOTO MAX POWERS?

10:32.465 --> 10:34.675
TRUST ME. YOU CAN'T.

10:37.345 --> 10:38.512
ALL RIGHT, MAX.

10:38.512 --> 10:39.555
GOOD TO MEET YOU.

10:39.597 --> 10:42.642
"I JUST WANT TO BEYOUR FRIEND."

10:42.683 --> 10:43.893
[PHONE RINGS]

10:43.934 --> 10:47.188
HOLD ON,I NEED TO TAKE THIS.

10:49.857 --> 10:51.400
HELLO, TOM.

10:51.442 --> 10:54.695
HEY. LISTEN, I FEEL BADABOUT OUR CONVERSATION BEFORE.

10:54.737 --> 10:56.030
I DIDN'T THINKMY MODE OF TRANSPORTATION

10:56.030 --> 10:57.406
WOULD UPSET YOU.

10:57.448 --> 10:58.282
WELL, IT DID.

10:58.324 --> 11:00.534
I MEAN, YOU HAVEFOUR DAYS TO SPEND

11:00.576 --> 11:02.203
WITH YOUR COVERED WAGON,

11:02.203 --> 11:04.080
BUT NO TIME FOR ME?

11:04.121 --> 11:05.623
WE REALLY NEEDTO DISCUSS THIS RELATIONSHIP.

11:05.664 --> 11:08.125
I WAS THINKINGTHE SAME THING.

11:08.167 --> 11:10.795
I AM SO HAPPYYOU FEEL THE SAME WAY.

11:10.836 --> 11:12.254
YEAH, I WAS HOPINGWE COULD TALK ABOUT IT

11:12.296 --> 11:13.881
WHEN I GET THERE?

11:13.923 --> 11:14.924
GREAT.

11:14.965 --> 11:16.467
OKAY, GREAT,I'LL SEE YOU SOON.

11:16.509 --> 11:19.345
BUT NOT TOO SOON, I GUESS.

11:31.899 --> 11:35.653
[♪♪]

11:35.695 --> 11:37.613
MERRY CHRISTMAS.

11:38.864 --> 11:39.782
HEY, TOM!

11:39.824 --> 11:41.909
HAVE A SEAT.

11:41.909 --> 11:43.244
THANK YOU, MAX.

11:43.244 --> 11:45.913
MY WRITER IS RUNNINGA BIT BEHIND.

11:45.913 --> 11:46.914
A FEW HOURS ON THE TRAIN,

11:46.956 --> 11:48.582
SHE'S ALREADYGOT WRITER'S BLOCK.

11:48.624 --> 11:50.251
[CHUCKLING]

11:50.292 --> 11:51.085
MERRY CHRISTMAS,GENTLEMEN.

11:51.127 --> 11:52.420
THANK YOU, ROXANNE.

11:52.461 --> 11:53.254
LET ME SEE...

11:53.295 --> 11:54.171
FOR YOU.

11:54.213 --> 11:55.172
OH, I NEEDED A PEN.

11:55.214 --> 11:56.173
MINE'S GONE AWOL.

11:56.215 --> 11:57.174
YEAH.

11:57.216 --> 11:58.467
OH, HERE SHE IS.

11:58.509 --> 12:01.137
THIS IS MY WRITER,ELEANOR CARTER.

12:04.890 --> 12:05.766
YOU TWO KNOW EACH OTHER?

12:05.808 --> 12:07.143
UH...

12:07.184 --> 12:08.519
-YEAH.-A LITTLE. NO.

12:08.561 --> 12:09.520
NOT REALLY.

12:09.562 --> 12:11.105
IT WAS A LIFETIME AGO.

12:11.147 --> 12:12.273
AND YET NOT LONG ENOUGH.

12:12.314 --> 12:13.315
ELLIE...

12:13.357 --> 12:14.900
NO ONE CALLS ME THATANYMORE.

12:16.402 --> 12:18.195
-UM...-TAKE A SEAT.

12:18.237 --> 12:19.196
DO I HAVE TO?

12:19.238 --> 12:20.197
I'LL GO.

12:20.239 --> 12:22.116
UH-UH, NOBODY'SGOING ANYWHERE.

12:22.116 --> 12:23.033
WHATEVER WENT ON

12:23.075 --> 12:23.951
BETWEEN YOU TWO

12:23.951 --> 12:24.952
IN THIS "OTHER LIFETIME,"

12:24.952 --> 12:27.496
THAT CAN BESETTLED HERE.

12:29.373 --> 12:31.125
BESIDES,

12:31.167 --> 12:33.753
IT'S ALMOST CHRISTMAS.

12:45.931 --> 12:47.641
I SEE YOU STILL HAVETHAT OLD NOTEBOOK.

12:47.683 --> 12:49.310
I SEE YOU'VE GIVEN YOURS UP.

12:49.310 --> 12:50.644
NOBODY USES PAPERANYMORE.

12:50.686 --> 12:52.313
AH, IT ALWAYS WORKED FOR ME.

12:52.354 --> 12:53.522
[MAX]:IPADS, PAPER...

12:53.564 --> 12:54.648
[CHUCKLES]

12:54.690 --> 12:55.983
WHATEVER GETSTHE STORY OUT, RIGHT?

12:56.025 --> 12:57.151
FUNNY,

12:57.151 --> 12:58.694
I NEVER WOULD HAVE PICTURED YOUIN HOLLYWOOD.

12:58.736 --> 12:59.904
AND I NEVER

12:59.945 --> 13:01.489
PICTURED THE MAN WHO WASGOING TO CHANGE THE WORLD

13:01.530 --> 13:03.157
WRITING ABOUT"HIS AND HER CLOSETS."

13:03.157 --> 13:04.575
OH, SO YOU READ IT.

13:04.617 --> 13:06.660
IN THE WAITING ROOMOF MY DENTIST'S, YEAH.

13:06.702 --> 13:08.037
YOU KNOW,

13:08.078 --> 13:10.331
THE INTERESTING THINGABOUT "HIS AND HER CLOSETS"

13:10.372 --> 13:12.583
IS THE "HER"DOESN'T GET UP AND RUN OFF

13:12.625 --> 13:14.168
WITHOUT EXPLANATION.

13:14.168 --> 13:16.504
AND THE "HIS" ALWAYSSTAYS SHUT AND EMPTY.

13:17.671 --> 13:19.673
YOU KNOW, I'M GOINGTO GET OFF AT THE NEXT STOP.

13:19.715 --> 13:22.134
THERE YOU GO,RUNNING OFF AGAIN.

13:26.555 --> 13:29.266
[MAX]: I'VE NEVERSEEN HER LIKE THAT.

13:29.308 --> 13:32.186
I'M AFRAID I...I BRING OUT THE WORST IN HER.

13:32.228 --> 13:34.855
I SHOULD GO AFTER HER...

13:34.897 --> 13:36.398
UNLESS YOU WANT TO.

13:37.358 --> 13:40.945
NO, I'M AFRAIDIT'S A LITTLE LATE FOR THAT.

13:58.003 --> 13:59.380
[MAX]:CAN I COME IN?

13:59.421 --> 14:01.340
SURE, MAX.

14:04.552 --> 14:05.970
YOU OKAY?

14:06.011 --> 14:07.721
YEAH.

14:07.763 --> 14:09.557
JUST KIND OF CAUGHT MEOFF GUARD, YOU KNOW?

14:09.557 --> 14:11.308
HMM.

14:11.350 --> 14:13.894
HE'S THE ONEYOU TOLD ME ABOUT?

14:13.894 --> 14:15.020
THE ONE THAT BROKE YOUR HEART.

14:19.733 --> 14:20.651
I'M SORRY.

14:20.693 --> 14:23.612
I HAD NO IDEA.

14:23.654 --> 14:25.865
MAX...HOW COULD YOU?

14:27.283 --> 14:30.286
ANYWAY, IT'S ANCIENT HISTORY.

14:31.287 --> 14:32.913
HOW LONG WERE YOU TOGETHER?

14:35.416 --> 14:36.417
SIX YEARS.

14:36.417 --> 14:38.252
THAT'S A LONG TIME.

14:39.587 --> 14:40.796
YEAH.

14:40.838 --> 14:42.590
WE MET ON ASSIGNMENT,

14:42.631 --> 14:43.799
TRAVELED THE GLOBE TOGETHER,

14:43.841 --> 14:45.467
FROM ONE WAR-TORN COUNTRYTO THE NEXT,

14:45.509 --> 14:47.886
TRYING TO CHANGE THE WORLD.

14:47.928 --> 14:49.597
HMM.

14:49.597 --> 14:52.600
ANYWAY, THAT KIND OF THINGTAKES ITS TOLL, YOU KNOW?

14:52.600 --> 14:54.184
BEING IN LOVE?

14:56.353 --> 14:59.148
I JUST COULDN'T LIVE LIKE THATANYMORE.

14:59.189 --> 15:00.357
APPARENTLY, HE COULD.

15:00.399 --> 15:01.942
HMM...

15:01.984 --> 15:03.527
BUT HE'S NOT NOW.

15:03.569 --> 15:05.946
THAT DOESN'T MATTER.

15:05.946 --> 15:08.282
I LEFT ALL THAT BEHINDWHEN I CAME TO WORK FOR YOU.

15:08.324 --> 15:10.284
SO WORKING FOR ME

15:10.284 --> 15:12.161
WAS AN ESCAPEFROM YOUR FEELINGS.

15:12.202 --> 15:14.955
HOLLYWOOD ISN'T REAL.

15:14.997 --> 15:17.166
MOVIES HAVE HAPPY ENDINGS.

15:17.207 --> 15:18.459
[CHUCKLES]

15:18.459 --> 15:20.794
WELL, MAYBE THIS IS FATE.

15:20.794 --> 15:21.879
NO, IT'S NOT.

15:21.921 --> 15:23.756
THIS IS BAD LUCK,THAT'S ALL.

15:26.717 --> 15:28.052
TOM LANGDON

15:28.093 --> 15:31.722
WAS THE BIGGEST MISTAKEOF MY LIFE.

15:37.061 --> 15:40.814
YOU, UH, SEEANYTHING OUT THERE?

15:40.856 --> 15:43.651
JUST A DARK NIGHT.

15:43.692 --> 15:47.488
MY WIFE USED TO SAY,

15:47.488 --> 15:48.530
"THERE NEVER WAS A PROBLEM

15:48.572 --> 15:51.617
THAT COULD DEFEAT SUNRISEOR CHRISTMAS."

15:53.494 --> 15:55.120
I'LL REMEMBER THAT.

15:56.664 --> 15:57.915
IS SHE TRAVELING WITH YOU?

15:57.956 --> 15:58.916
NO.

15:58.957 --> 16:02.086
SHE PASSEDA FEW MONTHS BACK.

16:03.045 --> 16:05.339
I'M SO SORRY.

16:05.339 --> 16:08.759
WE WOULD HAVEBEEN MARRIED 40 YEARS.

16:10.052 --> 16:11.971
A LIFETIME.

16:12.012 --> 16:13.514
MM.

16:15.057 --> 16:16.141
I'M GUESSING

16:16.183 --> 16:19.520
THAT YOU'RE HAVINGA PRETTY ROUGH NIGHT, TOO.

16:21.063 --> 16:23.691
THE DINING CAR TABLESARE PRETTY CLOSE.

16:23.732 --> 16:25.359
I SAW SOMEONEON THE TRAIN TONIGHT

16:25.359 --> 16:27.695
I NEVER THOUGHT I'D SEE AGAIN.

16:27.736 --> 16:29.363
ELLIE.

16:29.363 --> 16:32.449
"ELEANOR."

16:32.491 --> 16:33.492
AND SHE HATES ME.

16:34.493 --> 16:37.204
SHE DID SEEMA LITTLE UPSET.

16:37.204 --> 16:38.872
YEAH.

16:40.708 --> 16:43.210
WE DIDN'T HAVETHE YEARS TOGETHER YOU HAD,

16:43.252 --> 16:45.462
BUT WE WERE HAPPY.

16:46.839 --> 16:48.590
I THOUGHT WE WERE.

16:49.925 --> 16:51.135
WHAT HAPPENED?

16:51.176 --> 16:56.557
WE WERE IN JERUSALEM,COVERING A STORY,

16:56.598 --> 16:57.891
AND OUT OF THE BLUE,

16:57.933 --> 16:59.226
SHE SAYSSHE WANTS TO GO HOME.

16:59.268 --> 17:00.227
SHE ASKED METO GO WITH HER.

17:00.269 --> 17:02.229
SHE WOULDN'T EXPLAIN.

17:02.229 --> 17:06.233
I WAS STUBBORN.

17:06.275 --> 17:07.401
I WATCHED HERGET ON A TRAIN

17:07.443 --> 17:10.529
AND DISAPPEAR FROM MY LIFE.

17:14.324 --> 17:15.617
TOM LANGDON.

17:15.659 --> 17:18.328
JOHN KELLY.

17:22.290 --> 17:25.627
[♪♪]

17:28.881 --> 17:30.591
[TOM]:CHUGGING DOWN THE TRACKS

17:30.632 --> 17:33.469
IN 2,000 TONS OF PURE STEEL...

17:33.510 --> 17:35.929
[ELEANOR]:TRAPPED IN A TIN CAN...

17:35.971 --> 17:38.265
[TOM]:I ALWAYS HOPED I'D SEE HER AGAIN.

17:38.307 --> 17:39.600
[ELEANOR]:WITH THE ONE PERSON

17:39.600 --> 17:41.018
I NEVER WANTED TO SEE.

17:41.059 --> 17:42.186
[TOM]:WHY DO I SUDDENLY FEEL

17:42.227 --> 17:44.938
LIKE A WAR CORRESPONDENT AGAIN?

17:44.938 --> 17:48.108
[ELEANOR]:I NEED TO GET OFF THIS TRAIN.

17:59.119 --> 18:01.497
[P.A.]:TRAIN NUMBER 17 TO NEWARK

18:01.538 --> 18:03.290
NOW LEAVING BAY 2.

18:05.918 --> 18:07.711
A WINTER STORMIS PUSHING INTO THE ROCKIES.

18:07.753 --> 18:09.797
I THINK YOU SHOULD TAKE ONAN EXTRA ENGINE

18:09.838 --> 18:10.672
IN LA JUNTA.

18:10.714 --> 18:12.132
I'LL PASS THAT ALONG.

18:12.132 --> 18:13.258
THANKS, HIGGINS.

18:15.552 --> 18:16.720
THAT HIGGINS...

18:16.762 --> 18:19.973
ONCE A RAILROAD MAN,ALWAYS A RAILROAD MAN.

18:19.973 --> 18:21.350
WELL, HE SHOULDSTILL BE ONE.

18:21.391 --> 18:22.643
AS FAR AS I'M CONCERNED,

18:22.684 --> 18:24.311
HE KNOWS MORE ABOUT TRAINSTHAN ANYONE I HAVE EVER MET.

18:24.311 --> 18:25.479
WHY DID HE QUIT?

18:25.521 --> 18:26.480
OH, HE DIDN'T QUIT.

18:26.480 --> 18:27.564
THEY LET HIM GO.

18:29.024 --> 18:30.025
HEY!

18:31.735 --> 18:33.195
NORMAN! HOW'SYOUR MOM DOING?

18:33.237 --> 18:34.571
HOW DOES SHE KNOW EVERYONE?

18:34.613 --> 18:38.158
OH, SHE'S BEENRIDING THE TRAIN

18:38.158 --> 18:39.660
JUST ABOUTAS LONG AS I HAVE,

18:39.701 --> 18:41.870
AND I'VE HADA COURTSHIP WITH THIS ONE

18:41.912 --> 18:43.497
FOR 20 YEARS.

18:43.497 --> 18:44.832
ROXANNE?

18:44.873 --> 18:46.166
I SEEM TO HAVE LOSTA CHARM BRACELET.

18:46.166 --> 18:48.335
HAS ANYONE TURNED ONE IN?

18:48.377 --> 18:50.712
WELL, NO, NOT YET,MISS LARSON,

18:50.754 --> 18:52.422
BUT I'LL KEEPA LOOKOUT.

18:52.464 --> 18:53.549
THANK YOU.

18:53.590 --> 18:56.051
NO PROBLEM.

18:56.093 --> 18:58.178
HAVE OTHER PASSENGERSREPORTED THINGS MISSING?

18:58.220 --> 18:59.847
YOU TOO?

18:59.888 --> 19:01.348
WELL, IT'S JUSTAN OLD PEN.

19:01.390 --> 19:03.308
I CAN'T IMAGINE ANYONEWOULD TAKE IT.

19:03.350 --> 19:04.309
IT'S NOT WORTH ANYTHING,

19:04.351 --> 19:05.352
EXCEPT TO ME.

19:05.352 --> 19:07.062
WELL, I'LL KEEPA LOOKOUT.

19:07.104 --> 19:08.355
THANKS.

19:08.397 --> 19:09.940
WE LEAVEIN AN HOUR.

19:09.982 --> 19:11.191
DON'T MAKE MEHAVE TO COME FIND YOU.

19:11.233 --> 19:13.068
OKAY.

19:13.110 --> 19:16.238
["DECK THE HALLS" PLAYING,INSTRUMENTAL]

19:22.452 --> 19:24.538
[♪♪]

19:24.538 --> 19:25.914
EVERYTHING OKAY?

19:25.956 --> 19:26.874
IT'S TERRIBLE.

19:26.915 --> 19:29.042
IT'S JUSTA LITTLE SNAG.

19:29.042 --> 19:30.794
OUR MINISTERWAS SUPPOSED TO BOARD HERE,

19:30.836 --> 19:31.879
AND NOW HE'S NOT.

19:31.920 --> 19:34.381
HE SLIPPED ON THE ICEAND HE BROKE HIS ARM.

19:34.423 --> 19:35.507
IT'S A SIGN.

19:35.549 --> 19:38.218
IT SOUNDS LIKE WINTERIN THE MIDWEST.

19:38.260 --> 19:40.304
THIS WAS SUPPOSED TO BETHE HAPPIEST TIME OF OUR LIVES.

19:40.345 --> 19:42.055
[STEVE]:IT STILL CAN BE.

19:42.097 --> 19:44.433
NOT IF YOUR PARENTSHAVE THEIR WAY.

19:44.474 --> 19:46.685
YOUR PARENTS DON'T APPROVE?

19:48.353 --> 19:49.897
STEVE'S FATHERDOESN'T THINK I'M GOOD ENOUGH.

19:49.938 --> 19:51.607
THEY'RE HIGH-SOCIETYWASHINGTON,

19:51.648 --> 19:55.444
AND I'M JUST SOME GIRLFROM SMALL-TOWN KENTUCKY.

19:55.485 --> 19:57.529
I WORK AT HIS FIRM.

19:57.571 --> 19:59.072
HE SAID IT WOULD BEA BAD CAREER MOVE

19:59.114 --> 20:01.241
IF I DIDN'T STOPSEEING HER.

20:01.283 --> 20:03.911
WELL, 20 YEARS FROM NOW,

20:03.911 --> 20:06.538
YOU'LL BE MORE DISAPPOINTEDBY THE THINGS YOU DIDN'T DO

20:06.580 --> 20:07.581
THAN THE THINGS YOU DID.

20:08.707 --> 20:09.833
IS THAT FROMPERSONAL EXPERIENCE?

20:09.875 --> 20:11.084
NO.

20:11.084 --> 20:12.419
THAT'S FROM MARK TWAIN.

20:14.129 --> 20:15.088
YOU KNOW,

20:15.130 --> 20:16.465
MY GRANDMOTHERDID MARRY MY GRANDDAD

20:16.506 --> 20:17.674
IN A TRAIN STATION.

20:19.343 --> 20:21.803
[STEVE]: SEE, EVERYTHINGIS GOING TO BE JUST FINE.

20:37.069 --> 20:39.613
DID YOU, UH,GET YOUR FLIGHT OUT?

20:39.613 --> 20:42.032
I'M WORKING ON IT.

20:43.825 --> 20:47.371
I HEARD SOMEWHEREYOU GOT MARRIED.

20:47.412 --> 20:48.330
AND DIVORCED.

20:48.372 --> 20:50.123
OH. SORRY.

20:50.165 --> 20:51.792
IT'S OKAY.

20:53.502 --> 20:55.963
AND I TAKE ITYOU NEVER GOT MARRIED?

20:57.506 --> 20:59.841
NO, I'M SEEING SOMEONEOFF AND ON, IN L.A.

20:59.883 --> 21:00.842
MM-HMM?

21:02.386 --> 21:03.387
I GUESS

21:03.428 --> 21:06.139
SINCE THE CHANCESOF US EVER SEEING EACH OTHER

21:06.139 --> 21:07.015
AGAIN

21:07.057 --> 21:09.977
ARE PRETTY SLIM,

21:09.977 --> 21:11.520
CAN YOU TELL ME NOW?

21:11.561 --> 21:13.188
TELL YOU WHAT?

21:16.108 --> 21:17.359
WE WERE SO HAPPY.

21:17.401 --> 21:19.486
YOU JUST...WALKED OUT ON ME.

21:19.528 --> 21:20.821
IS THAT HOW YOU REMEMBER IT?

21:20.862 --> 21:22.572
THAT'S HOW IT WAS.

21:22.614 --> 21:23.573
I KNEW THIS WASGOING TO HAPPEN

21:23.615 --> 21:24.574
AS SOON AS I SAW YOU.

21:24.616 --> 21:25.575
I-- I KNEW--

21:25.617 --> 21:26.576
NO, ELLIE,I'M NOT TRYING TO--

21:26.618 --> 21:27.786
IT'S ELEANOR.

21:30.455 --> 21:31.581
FORGIVE MEFOR LIVING IN THE PAST

21:31.623 --> 21:32.874
WHEN YOU WERE JUST ELLIE.

21:35.043 --> 21:36.378
WE DIDN'T EVEN FIGHT.

21:36.420 --> 21:37.379
YOU JUST LEFT.

21:37.421 --> 21:40.716
IT'S NOT LIKEI SUDDENLY CHANGED.

21:40.757 --> 21:42.009
NO, TOM, YOU DIDN'T.

21:42.050 --> 21:43.093
YOU NEVER CHANGED.

21:44.970 --> 21:47.597
I GUESS I DID.

21:49.141 --> 21:51.059
♪ DECK THE HALLSWITH BOUGHS OF HOLLY ♪

21:51.101 --> 21:53.353
♪ FA-LA-LA-LA-LALA-LA-LA-LA ♪

21:53.353 --> 21:55.856
♪ 'TIS THE SEASONTO BE JOLLY ♪

21:55.856 --> 21:58.400
♪ FA-LA-LA-LA-LALA-LA-LA-LA... ♪

22:04.740 --> 22:06.867
[♪♪]

22:06.867 --> 22:08.660
[TRAIN CROSSING BELLS RINGING]

22:14.791 --> 22:15.834
YOU'RE UP LATE.

22:17.377 --> 22:19.379
YEAH. YOU TOO, AGNES.

22:19.379 --> 22:21.965
OH, I--I NEVER SLEEP.

22:22.007 --> 22:23.300
I WOULDN'T WANTTO MISS OUT ON ANYTHING.

22:23.342 --> 22:25.510
AND I'M SURE YOU HAVEN'T.

22:26.845 --> 22:29.431
I'M SORRY HOW THINGS WENTWITH ELEANOR,

22:29.473 --> 22:30.599
IN THE DINING CAR.

22:33.518 --> 22:35.312
NO SECRETSON A TRAIN,

22:35.354 --> 22:37.147
ESPECIALLY THE CHRISTMAS TRAIN.

22:37.189 --> 22:39.649
YEAH, I'M STARTING TO GET THAT.

22:41.234 --> 22:42.569
I'VE SEEN ENOUGH TO KNOW

22:42.611 --> 22:43.612
THAT TWO PEOPLE

22:43.653 --> 22:45.739
WHO CAN MAKE EACH OTHERTHAT MISERABLE

22:45.781 --> 22:48.325
MUST HAVE REALLY BEEN IN LOVE.

22:53.538 --> 22:55.749
SO ARE YOU SPENDING SOME TIMEWITH FAMILY

22:55.791 --> 22:57.459
FOR THE HOLIDAYS,

22:57.501 --> 22:58.794
SOMEWHERE ALONG THE LINE?

22:58.835 --> 23:01.588
NOT NECESSARILY.

23:01.630 --> 23:04.299
SO... YOU'RE JUSTRIDING THE TRAIN?

23:04.341 --> 23:06.093
IS THAT A PROBLEM?

23:06.134 --> 23:08.136
UH, NO. NO.

23:08.178 --> 23:11.014
JUST MAKING CONVERSATION.

23:13.892 --> 23:15.060
YOU HAVE A TREE.

23:17.771 --> 23:20.065
WOULDN'T BE CHRISTMASWITHOUT ONE.

23:23.068 --> 23:24.027
GOOD NIGHT, AGNES.

23:24.069 --> 23:25.112
GOOD NIGHT.

23:25.112 --> 23:26.029
THANKS.

23:29.825 --> 23:33.912
[♪♪]

23:40.419 --> 23:47.634
♪ CHRISTMAS IS ONLYA WEEK AND A FEW DAYS AWAY ♪

23:47.676 --> 23:50.887
♪ AND YOU HAVEN'TSEEN YOUR FOLKS ♪

23:50.929 --> 23:53.056
♪ SINCE THANKSGIVING DAY

23:53.098 --> 23:56.309
[♪♪]

23:56.309 --> 23:59.312
♪ I'LL SAY ITLOUD AND CLEAR ♪

23:59.354 --> 24:04.151
♪ I'LL SAY IT PLAIN

24:04.151 --> 24:07.320
♪ YOU WON'T WANTTO MISS THIS YEAR... ♪

24:07.362 --> 24:08.780
GOOD MORNING, TOM!

24:13.285 --> 24:14.911
[MAX]: GREAT NEWS.

24:14.953 --> 24:15.996
ELEANOR CHANGED HER MIND.

24:15.996 --> 24:17.664
SHE'S DECIDEDTO STAY ON

24:17.664 --> 24:19.332
AND CARVE OUT THE STORYWITH YOU.

24:19.332 --> 24:21.877
ACTUALLY,ALL THE FLIGHTS ARE BOOKED.

24:21.918 --> 24:23.920
EVERYTHING'S BOOKED SOLIDFOR CHRISTMAS.

24:23.962 --> 24:26.173
WELL, I LIKE TO SEE ITANOTHER WAY.

24:26.214 --> 24:28.925
MAX POWERSALWAYS GETS WHAT HE WANTS.

24:28.967 --> 24:31.511
[CHUCKLING]THAT'S RIGHT.

24:31.553 --> 24:33.346
PLEASE.

24:33.346 --> 24:37.559
SO YOU CAN CO-EXISTON THIS TRAIN

24:37.601 --> 24:39.186
FOR A FEW DAYS.

24:39.227 --> 24:40.520
ALTHOUGH IT DOES GETA LITTLE SMALLER

24:40.520 --> 24:42.856
THE LONGERYOU'RE ON IT.

24:42.856 --> 24:45.609
LIFE IS FULLOF FUNNY COINCIDENCES.

24:45.650 --> 24:47.194
YEAH.

24:47.194 --> 24:48.445
I WENT TO LUNCH

24:48.487 --> 24:50.780
IN AN EXPENSIVE CAFEIN BEVERLY HILLS

24:50.822 --> 24:51.948
A FEW MONTHS AGO,

24:51.990 --> 24:53.450
AND WHO'S THERE?

24:53.491 --> 24:56.286
NOT ONE, NOT TWO,BUT ALL THREE

24:56.328 --> 24:57.537
OF MY EX-WIVES.

24:57.579 --> 25:00.457
APPARENTLY,THEY MEET EVERY TUESDAY

25:00.499 --> 25:02.751
TO TALK ABOUT HOW AWFULIT WAS TO BE MARRIED TO ME.

25:04.044 --> 25:05.378
YEAH, SORT OF LIKEA BOOK CLUB.

25:05.420 --> 25:07.422
SO, TELL ME,

25:07.464 --> 25:09.216
WHAT HAVE YOU LEARNEDON THE TRAIN SO FAR?

25:09.216 --> 25:10.133
WELL...

25:12.302 --> 25:14.054
AH.

25:14.054 --> 25:15.305
THAT'S AGNES.

25:15.347 --> 25:18.099
SHE SEEMS TO KNOW EVERYBODYAND HAVE NO DESTINATION.

25:18.141 --> 25:20.435
SHE'S EITHER VERY NOSY,

25:20.477 --> 25:21.937
OR THERE'S SOMETHINGELSE GOING ON.

25:21.978 --> 25:23.146
MM.

25:23.188 --> 25:24.856
AND, UH...

25:24.898 --> 25:28.026
THAT'S MR. JOHN KELLY.

25:28.068 --> 25:32.405
HE'S LOST HIS WIFEAND, I SUPPOSE, HIMSELF.

25:32.447 --> 25:33.657
MISTY,

25:33.698 --> 25:35.784
WHO OFFERS UPRANDOM INFORMATION

25:35.825 --> 25:36.952
AND CALLS ITINTUITION.

25:36.993 --> 25:40.247
OH, AND WE HAVEA LOVE STORY ON BOARD, YEAH.

25:40.247 --> 25:41.248
STEVE AND JULIE.

25:41.248 --> 25:43.333
THEY'RE ELOPING.

25:43.375 --> 25:45.418
HE'S BIG-CITY SOCIETY,

25:45.460 --> 25:46.545
SHE'S SMALL-TOWN KENTUCKY,

25:46.586 --> 25:47.796
PARENTS DON'T APPROVE,

25:47.837 --> 25:49.589
AND THEY'VE LOSTTHEIR MINISTER

25:49.589 --> 25:50.715
AND THEY HAVE NO ONETO MARRY THEM.

25:50.757 --> 25:52.425
ALL OF THAT IN ONE DAY?

25:52.425 --> 25:53.927
HAS IT ONLY BEENONE DAY?

25:53.927 --> 25:54.761
[CHUCKLES]

25:54.761 --> 25:56.930
[WHISPERING] OH, AND...

25:56.972 --> 25:58.265
WE MIGHT HAVEA THIEF ON BOARD.

25:58.306 --> 26:00.267
I CAN'T FIND MY SUNGLASSES.

26:00.267 --> 26:01.268
BECAUSE YOU LEAVE THEMEVERYWHERE.

26:01.268 --> 26:02.269
OR BECAUSE

26:02.269 --> 26:03.436
SOMEONE TOOK THEM.

26:03.478 --> 26:06.106
OR YOU'RE CREATING A STORYWHEN THERE ISN'T ONE.

26:06.147 --> 26:08.149
